segment.source: The Server Groups Results pane in the Application Virtualization Server Management Console displays a list of the available server groups and Application Virtualization Management Servers.
segment.target: The Server Groups Results pane in the Application Virtualization Server Management Console displays a list of the available server groups and Application Virtualization Management Servers.

segment.source: When you right-click any server group, the following elements are displayed.
segment.target: When you right-click any server group, the following elements are displayed.

segment.source: New Application Virtualization Management Server
segment.target: New Application Virtualization Management Server

segment.source: Displays the New Server Wizard.
segment.target: Displays the New Server Wizard.

segment.source: Use this wizard to add a new Application Virtualization Management Server.
segment.target: Use this wizard to add a new Application Virtualization Management Server.

segment.source: This wizard has one page, in which you specify a name for the server in the Display Name field, and enter a name in the DNS Host Name field.
segment.target: This wizard has one page, in which you specify a name for the server in the Display Name field, and enter a name in the DNS Host Name field.

segment.source: From this wizard, you can also specify a maximum memory allocation for the server cache and a memory threshold warning level.
segment.target: From this wizard, you can also specify a maximum memory allocation for the server cache and a memory threshold warning level.

segment.target: New Window from Here

segment.source: Opens a new management console with the selected node as the root node.
segment.target: Opens a new management console with the selected node as the root node.

segment.source: Properties
segment.target: Properties

segment.source: Displays the Properties dialog box for the selected server group.
segment.target: Displays the Properties dialog box for the selected server group.

segment.source: The Properties dialog box has the following tabs:
segment.target: The Properties dialog box has the following tabs:

segment.source: General Tab—Enables you to select the provider policy from the drop-down list of provider policies and to enable or disable the server by selecting or clearing the Enable check box.
segment.target: General Tab—Enables you to select the provider policy from the drop-down list of provider policies and to enable or disable the server by selecting or clearing the Enable check box.

segment.source: Logging Tab—Displays the list of logging modules.
segment.target: Logging Tab—Displays the list of logging modules.

segment.source: You can add, edit, and remove logging modules from this tab.
segment.target: You can add, edit, and remove logging modules from this tab.

segment.source: When you add or edit a logging module, you can also set or change the logging level.
segment.target: When you add or edit a logging module, you can also set or change the logging level.

segment.source: Applications Tab—Lists the applications that are associated with the selected server group.
segment.target: Applications Tab—Lists the applications that are associated with the selected server group.

segment.source: The displayed information includes the application name, version number, and enable status.
segment.target: The displayed information includes the application name, version number, and enable status.
